President Biden met with President Ashraf Ghani and Chairman Abdullah Abdullah of Afghanistan. They discussed the enduring support of the United States for the Afghan people, including women, girls, and minorities. This support includes civilian, development, and humanitarian aid, as well as security assistance for Afghan National Defense and Security Forces. President Biden expressed concern about the increase in COVID-19 cases in Afghanistan and announced additional emergency U.S. assistance, including three million doses of vaccines. They emphasized the need for unity among Afghan leaders in support of peace and stability and reaffirmed the U.S. commitment to fully support intra-Afghan negotiations. Despite the withdrawal of U.S. troops, both sides agreed that the strong bilateral partnership will continue.